        Release Notes for BoxLib 16.12

The development branch was merged into master on December 2, 2016.

* Major Changes in C++ BoxLib

** C++11 is now required.
This may require some small changes in application codes.  Thanks to
C++11 rvalue ref-qualifier, flaws leading to potential dangling
pointers and references have been plugged.  A few bugs in Box are
fixed. 

** New I/O
Significant changes have been to I/O.  Many performance tuning
parameters have been introduced.  See Docs/Readme.io for details. 

** Make system
The make system has gone through a lot of cleanups.  See
Tools/C_mk/READ.md for details on the current make system.

